    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility evidence is sufficient for Medium model risk and Medium decision consequence. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved 2, required 3) is accepted because ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standardized test condition and no clinically relevant variation in loading rate exists. E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs confirms adequate predictive accuracy. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible for the stated COU.",
